<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1371" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1371">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source"><hi rend="smallcaps"><persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> Papers</hi></note>
                            <head>No. 1371<lb/><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the President’s Chief
                                    of Staff</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1"><hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1371fn1">From
                                    the fragmentary nature of this manuscript memorandum and its
                                    location in the <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>
                                    Papers, it seems probable that <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> wrote it and passed it to <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> during the course of the
                                    discussion of the Straits at the Eighth Plenary Meeting, July
                                    24. See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_366">p.
                                        366</ref>.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Potsdam</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-24">July 24 (?), 1945</date>.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Our attitude is<note n="2" xml:id="d1371fn2"><persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> originally wrote
                                    “should be”, but changed this wording to “is”.</note> free
                                passage of ships of all nations through the Straits on equal terms
                                and there should be no fortifications on the shores of the
                                Straits[.]</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>